1. What is this system?
This is a simple but smart online shopping website where you can:
Browse products
Add items to cart
Choose how to ship different-sized items (together or separately)
Pick a delivery speed (Standard / Express / Premium)
See exact arrival dates and total cost
Complete checkout (stock is automatically reduced)

2. How to Start the System
Step 1: Start the server

Open your terminal / command prompt.
Install Flask using "pip install flask"
Go to the project folder (the folder that contains app.py).
Type this command and press Enter:python app.py

You will see a message like:
Running on http://127.0.0.1:5000
Step 2: Open the website
Open any web browser and go to this address:
http://127.0.0.1:5000
The homepage will load automatically.

3. How to Use the Website
Step 1: Browse Products
You will see all available items with name, type, size, price, and current stock.
Stock numbers are shown in red.

Step 2: Add Items to Cart
For any product you want, enter the quantity.
Click the green “Add to Cart” button.
Repeat for other items.

Step 3: Manage Your Cart
Scroll down to the “Your Cart” section.
You can see everything you added.
Click the red “Remove” button if you want to delete an item.

Step 4: Choose Shipping Option (only appears if you have different sizes)
If your cart has items of different sizes (e.g. sofa + smartphone), you will see the Shipping Option section.
Choose:
Together → All items arrive on the same day (based on the largest item)
Separately → Each item arrives on its own day (smaller items arrive faster)

Click “Confirm Shipping Option”.

Step 5: Choose Transport Plan
Scroll to the Transport Plan section.
Pick one of the three plans:
Standard ($9.99)
Express ($19.99)
Premium ($39.99) – fastest option

Click “Select Plan”.

Step 6: Check Order Summary
Scroll to the Order Summary section.
You will see:
Subtotal
Transport cost (charged only once for the largest item)
Total price
Estimated arrival date(s)


Step 7: Checkout
Click the big “Checkout” button.
A success page will appear with your full order details.
Click “Go back for purchasing” to return to the shop.
You will notice the stock of purchased items has decreased.

Important Notes

Transport cost is charged only once based on the largest item (realistic shipping rule).
Arrival dates are calculated from today’s date.
Inventory is updated automatically after every successful checkout.
If an item’s stock reaches 0, it is still shown (future improvement will hide sold-out items).

Done!
